definition.value: Cytochromes of the c type that are found in eukaryotic MITOCHONDRIA. They serve as redox intermediates that accept electrons from MITOCHONDRIAL ELECTRON TRANSPORT COMPLEX III and transfer them to MITOCHONDRIAL ELECTRON TRANSPORT COMPLEX IV.

value.value: Gab proteins contain a pleckstrin homology (PH) domain and binding sites for SH2 and SH3 domains. Gab family include mammalian Gab1, Gab2, Gab3, Drosophila Dos, and C. elegans Soc1.
ISGF3 is a heterotrimer of STAT1, STAT2 and p48/ISGF3gamma/IRF9.
STAT1 dimers form the IFNgamma-activated factor (GAF).
